{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd69ba0e94a3c4025c78", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "A ball suspended by a thread swings in a vertical plane so that its magnitude of acceleration in the extreme position and lowest position are equal. The angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u03b8</mi><mo>)</mo></math> of thread deflection in the extreme position will be :", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "mXRv1", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "zqX0M", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "Rw7QX", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "ctkd5", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/c0232abe-07c6-4c67-b34e-10613ad1339e.png\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 215px;\"/></p><p>At the lowermost point, there is no tangential force on the ball. Thus, there exists no tangential acceleration at the bottommost point, only the centripetal acceleration survives.</p><p>On the other hand, in the extreme position of the ball, there is no centripetal acceleration as the ball becomes momentarily at rest at that position. Here, only tangential acceleration survives.</p><p>Thus, with respect to the figure above, equating the kinetic energy at the bottommost point to the potential energy at the extreme point, we have<br/><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>mv</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>mg</mi><mi>l</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>)</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Now, the net acceleration\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mfenced></math> at the extreme\u00a0point can be written as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>According to the given problem, it follows that for the two positions of the ball,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equations (1), (2) and (3) imply that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>)</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>\u03b8</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi>\u03b8</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mi>\u03b8</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>tan</mi><mfrac><mi>\u03b8</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "2dea04705e0942da98cd0250057e2dde", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/xIgrBX4mULAc0.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/xIgrBX4mULAc0.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "JEE Main (Imp. PYQs from 2023 - 2019)"}, "bucket": "Tough Ques (JEE Adv)", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ58385691", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fec2b295b085ab6eb8f"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c01d30997d3436baff", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", 